	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104220770339378><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=104220770339378>RE: battle tactics</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=104220770339378#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>809 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 10th 9:35 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Until you get to level 50+ the majority of your damage is going to be from normal melee attacks. You don't do a lot of damage per hit but you do get more hits than other classes over time(other than monks).&nbsp;&nbsp;So, get behind the mob and auto attack. Then backstab as your hot key allows. Your total damage output will be a bit higher than the tanks at level 20 and steadily increase compared to tanks as you get higher and higher in level.<br><br>Pick pocketing while grouped might get you in trouble. So, be careful about that.  Some mobs will scream &quot;Stop thief&quot; when picked, telling your group and anyone else nearby that you are picking pockets (orcs, gnolls, vendors, and guards are the most likely to rat you out).<br><br>If you have not set up an Evade hot key now is the time.  When soloing Evade is useless but when grouped it is very important.  You will draw aggro since you will outdamage the other melee classes.  Evade is the way you dump aggro back to the tanks.  Create a hot key that does<br><br>/attack off<br>/do ability #  (where # is the number of the skill button you have set up for Hide)<br><br>Call this hot key 'Evade' and do not ever lose it. When you are grouped and the mob starts wailing on you hit that Evade key.  As long as Hide is available (has recycled) there is a chance based on your Hide skill that you will push yourself down the hate list a few steps. Then the mob will turn on the person next highest on the hate list (hopefully not your group's cleric).  It doesn't always work but it is a help.<br><br>You will now be ready to make poison.  Don't get too excited about it unless you have PP to burn. It is expensive. The cheap ones (if you make your own vials) will cost you 3-4pp per dose.  Most mobs at that level don't drop that much loot. So, you are lucky to break even.  Save your money for a good weapon, AC/HP items and armor.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
